Why is it that the eyelids are often irritated and blush?
Answers ophthalmologist Tatiana Levashova:
Our eyelids are screens that protect the eyeball from the many small particles that settle on them.
Forgetting about the regular cleaning of the eyelids, we often contribute to the development of blepharitis.
The solution is simple:
Do not rub your eyes with dirty hands, carry a special wet wipe for the eyelids;
At least 1-2 times a day, clean the edges of the eyelids from the harmful substances accumulated in them during the day.
Cleaning procedures should be supplemented with warm compresses with decoctions of medicinal herbs (sage, chamomile), liquefying the thick secret of the sebaceous glands, and then massage the edges of the eyelids, which should be carried out with circular movements of the fingertips;
washing off makeup, do not use alcohol-containing products.
They dry and dehydrate the skin and contribute to even more thickening of the secretion of the sebaceous glands.
