This was reported to Izvestia by Assistant Minister of Economic Development Elena Lashkina.
In June 2015, Prime Minister Dmitry Medvedev, following a trip to the Crimea, instructed a number of departments - the Ministry of Economic Development, the Ministry of Transport, the Ministry of Culture, the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, the Ministry of Emergency Situations, the FSB, the Federal Customs Service, Rosturizm - to prepare proposals for creating favorable conditions for yachting in the coastal zones of the country.
