The Ministry of Transport instructed the captains of the seaports of Crimea to ensure the application of a simplified procedure for the entry of small-sized, sports sailing and pleasure vessels into the seaport and the exit of the listed vessels from the seaport.
Also, the Ministry of Transport has prepared draft orders of the Government of the Russian Federation on the approval of the boundaries of the water area of the seaports of Crimea.
In respect of Yalta and Feodosia, orders have already been adopted, the rest are in the process of coordination, the press service of the department noted.
