Prisons are being asked to create separate blocks for transgender people.
At the Public Council under the Federal Penitentiary Service (FSIN) for the protection of the rights of convicts in October 2015, among other issues, they will discuss the possibility of creating separate blocks for transgender and transvestites in the colonies.
This was told to “Izvestia” by a member of the Council Vladislav Grib.
According to him, depending on the total number of convicts in Russia who have not decided on gender, it is possible to provide separate cells, blocks or even (if there are many such criminals) in domestic prisons in the future to create a special colony for transsexuals.
However, Vladislav Grib emphasizes that it is possible to determine the serving of the punishment of citizens in such isolated places only after the convicts undergo appropriate medical examinations that prove that the offender is indeed a person who identifies himself as a member of the opposite sex.
Vladislav Grib is confident that isolating transgender people from other prisoners will ensure the safety of those serving sentences.
According to him, the proposed practice is successfully operating abroad: in the pre-trial detention center (where the accused are until the court decision) there are separate cells for transgender people, and in correctional institutions - special blocks.
This is the only way to deal with these criminals.
They should definitely be isolated, since the presence of transvestites and transgender people in ordinary cells is dangerous for them, it is suffering for their families and a sea of problems for the staff of the Federal Penitentiary Service.
The humiliation of trances on the part of fellow inmates is guaranteed, - says Vladislav Grib.
Depending on how large a city is, how many criminals with an uncertain gender, you need to calculate where to distribute them.
Individual detention facilities are not exactly needed - only cells, blocks in prisons.
Yes, a separate colony is possible if there are many transgender people.
According to Grib, the block can hold 50 or 100 people, and if a specialized corps is created in Russia alone, then transgender prisoners will be able to go there from any region.
Citizens are detained in the pre-trial detention center at the scene of the crime, so the arrival of transvestites or transgender people from other subjects during the investigation and trial is unrealistic, but to introduce such a practice for those already convicted in a separate colony - yes, - says Grib.
We will remind, on the eve of law enforcement officers could not decide in which detention center - male or female - to identify detained for drug possession 24-year-old transsexual Dmitry Kozhukov (known as Alina Davis), because of which the man with a girl's appearance was not arrested.
He was released home on a no-show.
This news was widely discussed in social networks and media, since there is really no mechanism for the detention of transgender people in prisons and colonies in Russia.
Russian human rights activist of LGBT movement (LGBT - lesbian, gay, bisexual, transgender) Nikolay Alekseev supported the idea of creating special places for serving sentences by transgender people, noting that abroad it is also possible to identify people in the colony - male or female - depending on their own desire.
Given the atmosphere in Russian prisons, the proposal is correct.
Yes, this is a very small percentage, but the problem exists, as well as the issue of ensuring security in prisons for homosexuals, - says Alexeyev.
Prisons need to be safe, so individual blocks could be made in the name of this and for homosexuals, especially since there are more of them in prisons than transgender people.
At the same time, Alexeyev doubts that there will be many citizens in Russia who are ready to impersonate transsexuals in order to get into a colony different from ordinary ones.
Of course, it is possible to introduce a medical examination before placing people in colonies for transgender people, but not always everything is unambiguous.
For example, in the United States, one of the prisoners Chelsea Manning looked like a man, and already in prison said that he wants to change sex, ”Alekseev said.
A person can feel like anyone.
But while there are no separate places to serve a sentence for transgender people, I doubt that prison staff will think seriously about the safety of such people and delve into the subtleties of their orientation or gender identity.
At the same time, Boris Lordkipanidze, an international expert on reproductive health issues in the Russian Federation, noted that the introduction of a new system of distribution of transgender criminals in the colonies can greatly delay the beginning of the serving of sentences by convicts.
A commission is being created - this is a matter of sexology, psychiatrists conduct long-term observations, this is not one test on the basis of which a high-precision conclusion is made.
Today’s mental health options allow it.
Therefore, before the change of sex, potential patients always undergo such examinations - they accurately show whether a change of sex with surgery is a necessary measure, - says Lordkipanidze.
However, it is difficult for me to imagine how to implement this system in relation to convicts, because on average such a survey takes a month.
The doctor, despite the fact that in general he supported the idea of creating separate blocks for transgender people, also doubts that in the current economic conditions it would be advisable to allocate funds for the construction of new premises, medical examinations, transgender units in Russia.
It is difficult to calculate, there are no official statistics, but if we take into account that there are about 5% of homosexuals in Russia, then we can say that there are even fewer transgender people, and there are quite a small number of those who have such a deviation and still commit crimes, ”Lordkipanidze said.
Now, at the request of the administration of the colony, homosexuals, transgenders and so can receive separate conditions of detention.
