This year, the study of the Association of Russian Managers "Top 1000 Russian Managers" is published for the 16th time.
Being a tool for assessing the professional reputation of Russian top-level managers, the study summarizes the work of Russian managers for the year, identifying leaders in industries and functional areas.
The initial pool of candidates consists of the winners of last year’s rating.
Last year’s winners are invited to confirm their participation as a candidate for this year’s rating and nominate members of their management team.
In addition, each of the candidates on the initial list is invited to nominate up to ten new managers from other companies, which it would be advisable to add to the general pool of candidates.
It is possible to nominate the following heads of functional areas of the company: financial director, commercial director, marketing director, HR director, CIO, director of public and corporate relations, director of relations with authorities, director of corporate governance.
Each manager proposed by experts is invited to participate in the rating and given the opportunity to nominate their management team and up to ten new managers from other companies.
Nomination of candidates on the industry principle is carried out on the basis of the industry classifier of the Association of Managers: information technology, commercial banks, forest and timber processing industry, engineering, media business, metallurgy, diversified holdings, professional services, communications and telecommunications, service and production of consumer goods, insurance, construction, trade, transport, financial sector, pharmaceuticals, chemical industry, energy and fuel complex.
Each participant is provided with a login and password to enter the site www.top1000.amr.ru, where they see information about the remaining participants and can put their ratings on the criteria proposed for each functional area.
The rating methodology is based on the principle "The best choose the best": top managers evaluate top managers, functional managers evaluate functional managers.
Such a principle allows you to get the most authentic assessment of the professional reputation of colleagues.
The final results of the rating are approved at meetings of expert commissions.
To the in-person meetings of expert commissions are invited all willing candidates of the rating of the current year and multiple candidates of the rating of previous years.
Commissions are organized on a functional basis: a commission for the approval of the list of top managers and eight commissions for the approval of heads of functional areas.
