The names of the companies are given in accordance with the rules of the Russian language and the norms of "Kommersant".
At the time of publication of the rating, changes in the status of managers and companies are possible.
The comfortable rate for an investment loan is 10-13%.
According to experts, the market of lending to small and medium-sized businesses in January-April of this year fell by 40%.
What do you think the situation is today?
After the panic of late 2014 - early 2015, the volume of lending to SMEs has decreased significantly.
The reason is clear: a sharp increase in interest rates.
Lending at 25-30% per annum was not beneficial to anyone.
If earlier the bank could lay in an increased rate all its possible problems in the future, from delays to non-returns, now it is impossible to do it: the rates are already sky-high.
For businesses, the current level of interest rates on SME loans is uncomfortable.
For a significant part of investment projects, the current level is unacceptable in terms of their payback.
A rate of 10-13% would allow businesses to invest in a wide range of projects and generate attractive returns on them.
How much do you think the demand for loans is being met?
After the reduction of the Central Bank interest rate, the situation has improved slightly.
Credit resources have become more accessible.
However, according to our observations, customers began to apply for loans much less often.
First of all, the business does not understand the prospects for its development and future income.
Today, business has one solution: it is necessary to learn how to work, focusing on the current economic situation in the country and the region.
It is necessary to monitor the current results more closely, control the cash flow.
At the same time, with the availability of financial resources, it is worth using new technologies to modernize equipment, reduce production costs and energy supply.
All this, ultimately, allows the company to make products more competitive and keep the business even in an unstable economic situation.
What are the main trends in the SME lending market that will strengthen and affect its development until the end of 2015?
Will the interest rate change?
The forecast for lowering the average rate will largely depend on the policy of the Central Bank, and now the regulator demonstrates consistency in the matter of lowering the key rate.
However, a radical fall in the price of loans for SMEs is not worth waiting.
In the current situation, the problem, first of all, is inflation, which makes it necessary to increase the interest rate to obtain real income.
In addition, the cost of money in Russia will remain high even with a decrease in Central Bank rates.
If we talk about the level of delay, traditionally small and medium-sized businesses, limited both in the possibilities of replenishment of funds and in the options for correcting economic behavior, will certainly represent a greater risk for creditors.
I would not expect a significant reduction in the share of bad loans.
The main reason is international sanctions and their negative impact on the country’s economy.
