Three mandates of “Fair Russia” go to Alexander Razumovsky, Igor Bogdanov and Mikhail Shalyugin.
Now, within five days, these candidates must decide whether they will work as deputies in the city Duma: in case of refusal of the mandate, he passes to the next candidate on the party list.
The chairman of the city election Commission Alexander Makeev told members of the Commission that introduces duty for “the distribution of telegrams Zhirinovsky and others” for the purpose of refusing mandates.
