The Duma introduced a bill on indexation of social pensions, taking into account the rise in prices.
The state Duma introduced a bill providing for the indexation of social pensions annually from February 1, taking into account rising prices.
The author of the document - MP from "Fair Russia" Alexander Lomakin-Rumyantsev - also proposes to conduct additional indexation of pensions on April 1, if the growth rate of the subsistence minimum exceeds the growth rate of prices for goods and services.
Indexation of social pensions, according to the current legislation, is carried out annually from April 1, taking into account the growth rate of the subsistence minimum of a pensioner in the Russian Federation over the past year.
The draft law submitted to the lower house provides for the introduction of indexation of social pensions, taking into account the growth rate of consumer prices.
At the same time, the first indexation is postponed to February 1, and the second is held on April 1.
