We can all come together to read, play, draw.
We made a play area for kids - the child comes just to play, and the hand still reaches for the book!
Some of our readers are carried away by their parents, and they are stooping with their legs, they do not want to leave.
Often come mothers with strollers - and we are pleased that they put the library in the first place among all the other places where you need to come with babies.
Tatyana Kushvid says: modern children just like we once loved classic children's literature:
"Publishing is now evolving, and much attention is being paid to authors who are the link between generations."
