Children do not like to part with their heroes.
The library constantly publishes booklets for parents, in which it tells what is happening in modern children's literature, which books are worth paying attention to and why.
Booklets are so fascinating and intriguing that adults are interested, but this library is still not for them.
Carrying books outside the reading room for adults is prohibited.
Only children have this magical privilege.
In the farthest room of the library there is a square hatch with an ancient wooden staircase to the basement, in the book depository.
The steps will scream under your feet - it's already a very old time machine.
With the book of your childhood, you meet like an old friend: hello, it's good that you and I do not change.
Ellie still walks along the road paved with yellow bricks, the lazy Tolya Ryzhikov steals magic matches, and Malcish-Kibalcish never told the damned bourgeois of Military Secret - he has such a firm word.
