There are also real book rarities in the repository - for example, a pre-revolutionary collection of epics with verses and eras.
Or the story of Korolenko in the famous appendix to the magazine "Niva".
Or a 1936 bursary.
Time has aged pages, painted them in tea color.
These publications are no longer given to readers.
These are fragments of our future collection, I all dream - I will retire and deal with rare children's books.
But the children will not behave at this, so to speak: and the colors in the old books are not very bright, and the topics ... you open the first page, and there - Lenin, the party, the Komsomol.
Now it seems: why did we all write out this “Pioneer truth”?
But it was still interesting, - says Galina Ilyasova, head of the book depository.
The pages of Murzilka have darkened from time to time.
Galina Vasilyevna has been in charge of the book depository all her life.
She knows what color Buratino's cap is, what school year Harry Potter became the captain of the Gryffindor team at the Quidditch Championship, in what situations Carlson uses a silencer for the motor, and who Alice Selezneva's father works for.
Little is paid for the work of a librarian, and everyone who can live without these book ranks very quickly finds another profession.
Only the most convinced remain: educators, educators, ministers of the cult of the book.
They can also be recognized by a smile - it is believed that this is a professional feature of a children's librarian.
If he smiled at you in the first minute of the conversation, it's a professional.
I generally love children's books: as a librarian I like them to be exactly and beautifully standing on the shelves, and I also love to read them, - says Galina Vasilyevna.
I read everything: military, historical stories, fairy tales, fiction.
Reading contemporary Russian authors, fresh translations...
Of course, I think everything was different in my childhood.
Books were the most interesting and exciting thing that ever happened to me.
And because I loved them so much, I thought the library was a magical place.
And I wanted to work where everyone was sitting and reading.
I hope there will always be books, despite the readers.
And I am happy when our former readers bring children, and even grandchildren ...
