The U.S. Embassy regrets the closure of the U.S. Center in Moscow.
The American Embassy in Russia expressed regret over the closure of the American Center at the Library of Foreign Literature.
The center worked in Moscow for more than 22 years.
The U.S. Embassy in Moscow deeply regrets the unilateral decision of the Russian government to close the American Center of the U.S. Embassy at the All-Russian State Library named after M.I.Rudomino in Moscow.
“The unilateral steps taken by the Russian Federation in recent years call into question the commitment of the Russian government to the ties between the Russian and American peoples, which were not interrupted even during the Cold War and at other difficult moments in the long history of relations between our countries,” US Ambassador John Tefft said in a statement to Interfax.
The American Center created deep and strong ties between people and culture of Russia and the United States.
It was the center of American culture, history and literature in the Russian capital, and also served as a venue for meetings with numerous American prominent figures, including cosmonauts, artists, athletes, scientists, politicians and writers.
“Last year alone, the American Center held more than 400 cultural and educational events and received more than 50,000 Russian visitors,” the diplomat said.
Tefft recalled that about a year ago it was decided to close another joint Russian-American project - the educational exchange program FLEX (Future Leaders Exchange Program).
The Green Tribunal was quick to strike.
A typical situation: four officials stand in front of Judge Swatanter Kumar’s desk, listening to his complaints about the work done.
The court is not satisfied with the quality of your work.
“We didn’t give you a 110-page order to make fun of him,” Kumar said.
If at least one more brick is put, we will order the demolition of all existing buildings.
Kumar heads the National Green Tribunal (NRT), a judicial body established in 2010 to stop the rapid pollution that has accompanied the rapid economic growth of recent decades.
During this time, the Tribunal has considered more than 10,000 claims related to air pollution, garbage collection, geological developments, toxic waste and dam construction.
In two of the three cases, the court decides to stop the construction leading to pollution.
The stakes are incredibly high: in the less than 60 years since the declaration of independence of enhanced industrial development, India has turned from a country of virgin jungles to one of the most overcrowded and polluted countries in the world.
The problem is particularly acute in large megacities, where infrastructure development does not keep pace with rapid urbanization: cities are covered with dense smog, rivers are filled with pesticides and waste of enterprises and households, and the few remaining residential areas are cut down for development by new residential areas.
Despite the formal support of the state for the green movement, the NZT is regularly criticized by the Narendra Modi government, as it often becomes the main reason for the cancellation of major investment projects.
So, in May this year, the Minister of the Environment called the court’s decisions “extreme” and “impossible”.
Sometimes court decisions are really impossible to enforce within the time limit set by the court, confirms environmental lawyer Raj Panjwani.
However, impossible deadlines have a positive side: at least they force the responsible persons to move.
“His main goal is to shake up this system,” the lawyer adds.
The Green Tribunal has repeatedly cancelled major construction projects: it has stopped the construction of the airport, the power plant and hundreds of smaller structures.
At the same time, people are also trying not to forget: for example, during the discussion of the fate of a pharmaceutical company in the state of Telagana, which polluted the local river with fluoride.
We may close your factory, but we are also responsible for the economic consequences.
“People will lose their jobs,” Kumar said.
However, such explanations are not always understood by ordinary people, whose lives can change thanks to one stroke of the judge’s pen.
Thus, in April, the Tribunal decided to ban all vehicles older than 10 years from entering the capital, which caused public outrage.
Despite sharply falling popularity and a flurry of criticism, Swatanter Kumar refused to cancel this decision.
Instead, he ordered statistics from the Delhi government on incoming and outgoing vehicles, and also made a proposal to purchase 10,000 additional buses, having previously found out in factories whether they were able to fulfill such an order.
As pollution sources such as landfills, fuel quality and even road accidents began to come to the attention of the courts, popular anger began to subside.
But the most painful topic of the principled judge was the program to clean up the Ganges River, pompously announced by Prime Minister Narendra Modi last year.
When it comes to the Ganges, a sacred river for Hindus, the judge often stops restraining his emotions and turns to screaming.
Do you know what the word "saint" means?
Someone poured water from the Ganges on the statue of God, and in it were feces, - the judge is excited.
You keep polluting the river because you think: Ganges is Ganges, it will take away all our sins.
This is the river we worship and see what you do with it every day.
Cleaning up the Ganges is the most ambitious and expensive environmental project announced by the new government.
Currently, the number of fecal bacteria in this river exceeds the norm by more than 120 times.
Every year, 1.5 to 3 of the 700 million Indians who swim in it die from infectious diseases.
In February, Narendra Modi even donated money to the Ganges Rescue Fund from the sale of his suit, in which he met with Barack Obama and 455 other items from his personal collection.
Environmentalists immediately accused the prime minister of populism: the suit was bought for 700 thousand dollars, while it takes at least eight billion to clean the river.
Supporters of the Green Tribunal agree that India still has a long way to go before it can call itself a developed country, but do not believe that the price of progress should be the environment.
“In a developing country, talking about the environment is often seen as an unacceptable luxury,” says Call Gang activist Malika Bhanot.
And the court is trying to find a middle ground between ecology and development.”
A man poured blood on several paintings of Dali at an exhibition in Riga.
A visitor to the exhibition of the Latvian Union of Artists in Riga broke the windows in the museum and ruined the sculpture of Salvador Dali “The Appearance of an Angel”.
Now the museum hosts an exhibition of works by Salvador Dali and Pablo Picasso.
A man born in 1985 entered the sculpture hall at 2:20 p.m.
He immediately behaved inadequately: he ruined the sculpture, broke the windows.
Then he began to move around the premises and stained with blood several works of permanent exposure.
Among them is a portrait of Poruk by Miervaldis Polis.
According to the President of the Latvian Union of Artists Igor Dobychin, to whom Interfax refers, the shop windows were also spoiled.
Police and art experts work at the scene.
The latter determine the extent of damage and damage.
A criminal case of hooliganism has been initiated against a man.
In the Latvian Union of Artists from August 4 to September 27, an exhibition of works by Picasso and Dali is held, which presents more than 200 original works of artists.
Commentator Gennady Orlov hospitalized in Spain.
On Wednesday, Russian champion Zenit from St. Petersburg will hold its first match of the group stage of the Champions League with the Spanish “Valencia”.
Unfortunately, the game of St. Petersburg will not be able to comment on Gennady Orlov.
Commentator channel NTV Gennady Orlov was hospitalized on Wednesday in one of the Spanish clinics with suspected acute appendicitis.
The survey will give an answer - whether seventy-year-old Gennady Sergeyevich needs surgical treatment.
Commenting on the match will be Konstantin Genich.
“Zenit” is in the Champions League group.
His rivals are the Spanish Valencia, the French Lyon and the Belgian Gent.
Volgograd Governor and akim of West Kazakhstan region signed a cooperation agreement.
On September 16, the XII Forum of Interregional Cooperation between Russia and Kazakhstan was opened in Sochi.
The key theme is cooperation in the agro-industrial complex and ensuring food security.
The work of the international forum is also attended by the Governor of the Volgograd region Andrei Bocharov.
It should be noted that Kazakhstan is one of the strategic partners of our region.
Annually, economic cooperation is increasing, as well as cultural ties.
On September 16, Andrei Bocharov and akim of the West Kazakhstan region Nurlan Nogayev signed a cooperation agreement.
The document will create favorable conditions for the mutual supply of goods, as well as increase the interaction of industrial enterprises.
The Russian-Belarusian exercise "Union Shield-2015" is over.
In the west of the country ended the joint Russian-Belarusian exercises “Shield of the Union-2015”, reports “Russia 24”.
The maneuvers took place at landfills in the Leningrad, Pskov and Kaliningrad regions, as well as in the Baltic Sea.
More than eight thousand servicemen and about four hundred units of equipment participated.
On the last day of the exercises, the ships of the Baltic Fleet worked out an artillery strike on sea and coastal targets, as well as a reflection of an air attack by a conditional enemy.
Where can I leave a comment about the work of the bailiff in Murmansk?
The Department of the Federal Service of bailiffs in the Murmansk region reported that to improve the protection of the rights and legitimate interests of citizens and organizations in the department there is a book of reviews and proposals.
In it, citizens can leave a record of the quality of the work of bailiffs-executors and other management officials, information about shortcomings in the work, as well as express their suggestions and wishes.
In management, a copy of the book of reviews and offers is located in the central hall, in a special pocket in a visible and accessible place at the checkpoint to the building.
In the structural units of the office, the book is in the office.
In view of the nature of the withdrawal or proposal, a written response shall be sent to the proponent, as appropriate.
Xi Jinping calls for economy to be more open to the world
The economy must become more open to the world to spur growth, President Xi Jinping said on Tuesday in an address to a group tasked with leading reforms.
“China should focus on attracting foreign investors and experts and develop a policy of openness,” he said, addressing the participants of the 16th meeting of the Committee of the Central Leading Group on Comprehensive Deepening of Reforms.
According to him, the expansion of openness and deepening of reforms will give the economy a new impetus and vitality and will provide new space for economic development.
The lead group adopted a number of directives, including the introduction of regulation of investor access to the market, changes to border controls, the encouragement of state-owned enterprises (SOEs) to attract private capital and the revision of the resident registration system.
According to the statement, a list of sectors of the economy and production that are not available for investment will be compiled.
The system will be gradually debugged through trial programs.
This is an important step, as it will give the market a more significant role in the allocation of resources, ensuring the rule of law in the business sphere and increasing openness, according to the statement.
The government will also loosen control over the powers it gives to companies, thereby ensuring that companies do their own business.
The statement also said that China will allow border regions to develop new models of cross-border economic cooperation and new mechanisms to strengthen local growth.
Even more areas will be available to private investors in order to increase the openness of state-controlled sectors of the economy.
“The government will not change its policy towards foreign investors and will protect the legitimate interests of companies with foreign financing, as well as provide them with better conditions,” the statement said.
In addition, the procedure for applying for a permanent residence permit for foreigners, or “green card”, will be facilitated by optimizing the requirements and simplifying the filing process itself.
The meeting also discussed ensuring the rights of lawyers and issues of training professional judges and prosecutors.
According to the official report released after the meeting, it was also attended by Prime Minister Li Keqiang and ministers Liu Yunshan and Zhang Gaoli.
